text: a baker who had a very bad , violent temper , and whenever a batch of bread was spoiled
a tiny thin black man , no thicker than an eel , with long arms and legs
The first person who tasted the bread
The next person to eat the bread
a man who had broken his leg
a young couple , who were newly married , and were as happy as the day was long
a man who wants to be unhappy
a husband who does not like being happy
a large pleasant farmhouse , standing amongst fields
the largest farm in all the country round
a man who says he has nothing to complain of
